These rebels sail north and land upon a virgin shore, where they are forced to build a nation from nothing. But how do they establish a civilization that will stand the test of time?

Once allies against the Unholy King, the rebels have different ideas about how best to build their nation from nothing – through military might, through religious zealotry, or rejecting both – and everyone is willing to fight for their own ideas.

The Unholy King may be searching for them. Foreign neighbors may appear on their unsecured border at any hour. Their limited food stores are running out faster than makes sense. The world may prove much larger than any of them expected. Traitors may live in their midst.

Split into four parts, this political fantasy novel mixes mystical magic with medieval political intrigue. Enter this otherly world and find out which men and women are worthy to be etched in the annals and become the heirs of history.', 'In a reversed-sun fantasy world, rebels escape an unholy king and his sorcerer priests to forge a new nation on untouched lands amid civil strife.', 2021, NULL, '9798541636147', 299, NULL, NULL, '/uploads/covers/cover-1774061655402.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'July 21, 2021', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'the-heirs-of-history-a-nation-from-nothing-t-josiah-haynes', 0, 'manual', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 14:53:21', '2026-03-22 20:32:05');
